# IMAGE QUALITY SETTING (Still Photography)

## COLOR CHROME FX BLUE
Increase the range of tones available for rendering blues.

| Option | Description                |
|--------|----------------------------|
| STRONG | Choose for a strong effect.|
| WEAK   | Choose for a weak effect.  |
| OFF    | Turn the effect off.       |

## WHITE BALANCE
For natural colors, choose a white balance option that matches the light source.

| Option                      | Description                                                                 |
|-----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| !WB AUTO WHITE PRIORITY | White balance is adjusted automatically. Choose for whiter whites in scenes lit by incandescent bulbs. |
| AUTO                        | White balance is adjusted automatically.                                    |
| !WB AUTO AMBIENCE PRIORITY | White balance is adjusted automatically. Choose for warmer whites in scenes lit by incandescent bulbs. |
| !Custom1 CUSTOM 1        | Measure a value for white balance.                                    |
| !Custom2 CUSTOM 2        | Measure a value for white balance.                                    |
| !Custom3 CUSTOM 3        | Measure a value for white balance.                                    |
| !K COLOR TEMPERATURE     | Choose a color temperature.                                           |
| !Daylight DAYLIGHT       | For subjects in direct sunlight.                                      |
| !Shade SHADE             | For subjects in the shade.                                            |
| !Fluorescent1 FLUORESCENT LIGHT-1 | Use under "daylight" fluorescent lights.                              |
| !Fluorescent2 FLUORESCENT LIGHT-2 | Use under "warm white" fluorescent lights.                            |
| !Fluorescent3 FLUORESCENT LIGHT-3 | Use under "cool white" fluorescent lights.                            |
| !Incandescent INCANDESCENT | Use under incandescent lighting.                                      |
| !Underwater UNDERWATER   | Reduces the blue cast typically associated with underwater lighting.  |
